cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the spectral response of CNNs, which is related to their internal workings and learning process, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper proposes using the gain of CNNs as a diagnostic tool, which is a practical application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) techniques.
